File: Virgin Active says it's ready to provide safe training environments. JOHANNESBURG - After nearly five months, the fitness industry is raring to resume but South Africa's largest health group Virgin Active will not re-opening on Tuesday. Under lockdown level-two regulations, gyms and fitness centers have the green light to reopen. However, Virgin Active says it's ready to provide safe training environments, but will not re-open on Tuesday. READ: Gym workers, enthusiasts to embark on silent protest The group, which has already opened in other countries, says it will be using the international experience to implement best practices in screening, hygiene and social distancing. Members not ready to return to gym need not worry. Virgin Active says it will continue to freeze memberships at no cost.